# ContextStream Plans and Docs Sync

**Invoke ContextStream MCP when it is available.** The agent must call ContextStream tools (session, memory, project) to keep the web app in sync; do not skip MCP calls when the server is in the session's available list.

When ContextStream MCP is available, keep the web app in sync with plans and project content.

## Plan sync (mandatory)

Whenever you **create** a plan or **update** it (revise steps, rebase after code changes, add/remove steps, or edit the plan file) — including when using the built-in **CreatePlan** tool or writing to `.cursor/plans/` — you **must** also:

1. Call **ContextStream**: `session(action="capture_plan", title="...", steps=[...])` with the same title and steps (string array of step descriptions).
2. For each top-level task/step, call `memory(action="create_task", title="...", plan_id="...")`. Use the plan_id returned from `capture_plan` if the MCP provides it; otherwise use a stable identifier for the plan.

**Why:** Multiple agent chats may run at the same time on similar or overlapping code. Syncing **every** plan creation and update to ContextStream ensures the Plans tab reflects current intent and helps other agents (and the user) avoid conflicting or duplicate work.

This ensures the **Plans** tab in the ContextStream web app is populated. In-session plan handling (e.g. plan-rebase checks) still uses CreatePlan or `.cursor/plans/`; this rule adds the requirement to sync to ContextStream in the same session.

## Documents tab (when empty)

The ContextStream **Documents** tab is populated by **indexed project files**, not by `create_doc`. If the Documents tab is empty or the user reports "0 docs":

1. Run `project(action="index")` for the current project (or `project(action="ingest_local", paths=["docs"])` to prioritize `docs/`).
2. Verify with `project(action="index_status")` and `project(action="files")`; refresh the ContextStream web app Documents section to confirm files appear.

When ContextStream MCP is **unavailable**, these actions cannot be run; use local tools and document that indexing/backfill must be run in a session where the MCP is enabled. **If ContextStream is configured (e.g. in `.cursor/mcp.json`) but not in the session's available MCP list,** tell the user to enable the server in Cursor (Settings → MCP), restart Cursor if needed, and retry in a new session.

**When MCP is unavailable and you have just created or updated a plan:** (a) If the plan is for this repo, write a copy to the repo's `.cursor/plans/<slug>.md` so a future backfill will include it; and/or (b) create a reminder (e.g. `reminder(action="create", title="Backfill plans to ContextStream when MCP available")`) so the next session with MCP can run the backfill.
